Male genitalia (
Figs 6–12
). Genital segment about 1.45 times higher than wide. Anal segment about 2.8 times longer than wide, distal portion slightly bent ventrally, laterodistal margins slightly asymmetric. Parameres moderately long, narrow in basal half, then gradually expanding. Aedeagus basal part (shaft) slightly compressed, slender; ventrally near base two minute, rigid spines directed proximally, right margin forming almost at distal half a rounded projection directed laterally; dorsal side of basal part subapically forming a weak concave depression. Shaft apically with three movable spinose processes: left lateral one moderately curved directed basally; right lateral one slightly sinuate, in repose directed basally; ventral one bi-forked, left tine shorter, right tine almost twice as long as the left one. Distal part of aedeagus (velum) apically curved, in repose reflected basally with the tip fitting the hollow at dorsal base of shaft.
